shingle country
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:steep, barren high-altitude land of the South Island, often with faces of sharp and angular running shingle.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
